# [Rationale]: Declarative infrastructure for macOS GTM Ops workstation (2026).
# Homebrew is strictly limited to OS-level system dependencies and GUI Casks.
# Pure CLI tools have been migrated to the hermetic 'mise' toolchain.

# System Cryptography & Certificates
# [Rationale]: Pre-condition the environment to ensure modern crypto standards for tools like mise.
# [LLM Context]: This is critical for resolving ECDSA public key parsing errors in headless CI runners.
brew "ca-certificates"
brew "openssl@3"

# Core System & Network
brew "git"
brew "socat"

# Media & Document Processing
brew "imagemagick"
brew "ghostscript"
brew "tectonic"

# Casks (GUI Apps & Fonts)
cask "1password-cli"
cask "font-jetbrains-mono-nerd-font"

# [Rationale]: WezTerm Stable is too dated for modern Kitty graphics extensions.
# wezterm@nightly provides the necessary protocol implementation for snacks.nvim.
cask "wezterm@nightly"
